<tr><td align = left><font color = #394a54 face = "Arial" size = +3><b>September is Pokémonth!</b></font><br><br></td></tr>
<tr><td>
<table border = 0 width = 100% align = center><tr>
<td valign = top><img src = ../generalimages/1471459748.png hspace = 10 vspace = 10 border = 0 alt = '' align = left>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<br><font color = # face = "Arial" size = +2>Pokémon is taking over Cumberland Public Libraries this September!
<br>
<br>
Ages 3 - 18 can take part in a <b>Pokémon Scavenger Hunt</b> at all library locations. From September 1 - 30, you can go to your local branch and ask at the desk for a Pokédex. Catch them all to win a book prize!
<br>
<br>
Be sure to check out the <b>Pokémon Parties</b> happening at every branch in September! There will be Pokémon-inspired crafts and games for kids in Grades P-6. (Note: we will not be playing Pokémon Go.) See the <a
href="http://cumberlandpubliclibraries.ca/index.php?pagecontentid=207&demoid=1&linkid=3&menuid=1">Calendar of Events</a> or contact your local library for dates and times.
<br>
<br>
Need a crash course in Pokémon Go? Adults are welcome to attend our <b>Pokémon Go for Parents</b> session at the Four Fathers Library from 6:00-7:00 on September 13.
<br>
<br>
<h3 align="center" class="headerline"> </h3>
</font></td>
</tr></table>
</td></tr>

